xonshbot: IRC <-> Gitter.im bridge

RUNNING

Simply run the following, command after setting the environment variables
discussed below:
   $ xonsh xonshbot.xsh


xonshbot needs some important configuration to work as expected.  Options are
controlled by the following environment variables:

   * $GITHUB_URL: The URL to the root Github repo WITH TRAILING SLASH
                  (e.g., "https://github.com/xonsh/xonsh/")

   * $GITTER_APIKEY: The API key of the Gitter account the bot should use
   * $GITTER_ROOM: The URL of the Gitter room the bot should enter (e.g.,
                   "xonsh/xonsh")

   * $IRC_HOST: The irc host to connect to (e.g., "irc.oftc.net")
   * $IRC_PORT (optional): The port number (if not specified, 6667 will be
                           used)

   * $IRC_CHANNEL: The irc channel to join (e.g., "#xonsh")
   * $IRC_NICK: The irc nick the bot should use (e.g., "lou-carcolh")
   * $IRC_PASSWD: The password associated with the bot's nick


